cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "staff-engineer-mode: a Claude Code skill for principal-engineer thinking"
message: >-
  If you use this skill in your work or write about it,
  please cite both this software AND the underlying source
  books (see NOTICE for full ISBN attributions).
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Francisco
    family-names: Lopes
    affiliation: Independent
repository-code: "https://github.com/franciscolopes26/staff-engineer-mode"
url: "https://github.com/franciscolopes26/staff-engineer-mode"
abstract: >-
  An operating-mode skill for Claude Code that activates
  principal-engineer thinking on non-trivial coding tasks.
  Enforces a 5-phase loop (UNDERSTAND, SPECIFY, PRE-MORTEM,
  CHANGE, VERIFY), a 30-item red-flag detection catalogue
  with restart actions, the 3-strike rule, cognitive layers
  for software thinking and attack-surface thinking, and
  paste-able templates per phase. Grounded chapter-by-chapter
  in 10 canonical software-engineering books.
